description:
They actually pay out $13,000 per diagnosis and $39,000 if they are put on ventilators. If you dont think this is the reason for the disproportionate numbers then the flouride is working . Not many people know this about me but I work in healthcare and this kind of stuff (inflation of numbers for bigger payouts) happened and happens ALLL the time . The good thing is that now the real data is starting to come in and show that countries who did not lockdown or quarantine were not only better off but now have a majority of the population that is immune to the illness . .
